//what's triz Teoriya Resheniya Izobretatelskikh Zadatch (TRIZ) TRIZ is one of the methods introduced by Genrikh Saulovich Altshuller by offering 40 principal solutions to overcome the contradictions of the problems that occur from 39 existing parameters. Altshuller has analyzed 200,000 existing patents and then he made a pattern of solutions to the problems solved by these patents. After that, from these strong patterns Altshuller collected them again into 40,000 patents. From the 40,000 patents with strong patterns that he got, Altshuller concluded that there are cause variables called 39 system parameters and solution variables for each problem called 40 principal solutions. TRIZ provides great principles and concrete tools for creative thinking in a range of technologies.\n TRIZ is also widely used in various technical and business worlds in many industries to assist in the generation of solutions to problems. Therefore, Altshuller introduced the TRIZ method with 39 parameter systems and 40 Solution Principals which have been compressed from 40,000 existing patents.\n TRIZ is a philosophy of science and technology method with a systematic and structured way of thinking to find creative and innovative development solution ideas to a problem, a system that includes knowledge technology for databases. TRIZ can be used in creating new products to generate product innovation ideas or ideas to make the innovation process more effective and efficient such as reducing operational costs or expenses. Video References Source :
//39 System Parameter 39 System Parameter The Parameter The principle of 39 System Parameters in TRIZ are standard problem types used for crystallized problems and what variables conflict with each other. This principle is the fundamental consideration for identifying system parameters that are improving and worsening. These parameters are then compared against each other to form the TRIZ contradiction matrix(San, 2019). Meaning Synonyms, Antonims, and Equivalent meanings
//40 Inventive Principles 40 Inventive Principles The Principles The Principle of 40 Principal Solutions in TRIZ is used to provide solutions to overcome the intersection that occurs between system parameters. This principle is the basis consideration of the problem solving pattern(San, 2019). Solutions Illustrations Illustration
//Business and Management How can it Work in Business and Management TRIZ for Business and Management Are you ready to face new challenges to grow your business? Are you able to develop new breakthrough ideas that can give you an edge over the competition? TRIZ can be used to assist in developing innovative ideas for business strategies effectively and efficiently. TRIZ in Business In an effort to generate new product introduction is a radical innovation process, Obviously the process is not efficient at all. Because very limited resources will cause very expensive costs in developing new products coupled with a high risk of success. The worst case scenario is when you find that the product is not accepted in the market. There needs to be a better way than just a trial and error brainstorming approach to generating ideas. We need to use structured and systematic tools like TRIZ to reduce the quantity of effort, while increasing the quality of ideas. This reduces time and resources for new product validation and success. Business people who can adopt this method and improve their innovation process efficiently can have a high chance to compete with competitors. TRIZ in Management Roles in management typically involve leading and coordinating a group of people to achieve a set of goals or objectives. In the process of achieving this goal or objective, the group will very often need to tackle a range of simple to complex problems. In most cases, management problems are complex and have multiple root causes. The root causes are not easily identified and are interrelated where improvements in one area can lead to improvement but also give rise to worsening problems in different areas. This is an often overlooked contradiction. Problems with multiple root causes cannot be solved through conventional methods. it will be essential to equip the management team with sophisticated problem solving techniques such as TRIZ to solve complex problems. It has been proven that technical methodologies and tools can be borrowed and used effectively to assist in the field of management. Management teams that can solve complex problems and are able to cope with increasing complexity will have an added advantage in a globalized future.
//Contradiction Matrix Material Contradiction Matrix The TRIZ method uses the principle of matrix contradiction as an initial analysis in finding the recommended solution results offered by the TRIZ method and is obtained from the technical intersection between the increasing parameter and the deteriorating parameter. The intersection technique works with when trying to increase a system parameter, other aspects will decrease. The intersection is determined by using the concept of 39 parameter systems in the TRIZ method. Based on the 39 parameter systems, the contradiction matrix records 4 principal solutions for each type of problem in the form of a 39x39 table. The contradiction matrix will identify to provide solution recommendations based on 40 solution principals that have the potential to solve existing problems according to a predetermined parameter system. The contradiction matrix is used as the core in the database in this application. The expression of technical contradiction is in the form of: if the manipulative variable changes, the response variable #1 increases, but the response variable #2 worsens. Example: If more incentives are given to employees, then employee retention increases but this will complicate the company compensation and benefits operations: Based on the predetermined parameters, the recommended inventive solution principles are as follows: (2), (35), (22), (26) Case Study How to Use
